{"expireTime":9007200869552456000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-6ceac412e0b7dd60f557b09480155677--","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Book in 3 Sentences","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":5,"offset":5},"end":{"line":2,"column":28,"offset":28},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":28,"offset":28},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Being rational is a way to make our beliefs about the world more true, which matters so that we can better influence things in the ways we see fit.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":30},"end":{"line":4,"column":148,"offset":177},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":30},"end":{"line":4,"column":148,"offset":177},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"We know about many of our biases, but this is not enough to overcome them, and we must be attentive and actively try to spot our biases in the moment or we will fall for them.","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":179},"end":{"line":6,"column":176,"offset":354},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":179},"end":{"line":6,"column":176,"offset":354},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are many ways we convince ourselves that we know more than we do, and we must repeatedly ask ourselves what the evidence is behind our believes, and what outcomes our beliefs predict in the real world.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":356},"end":{"line":8,"column":208,"offset":563},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":356},"end":{"line":8,"column":208,"offset":563},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My Top 3 Quotes","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":5,"offset":569},"end":{"line":10,"column":20,"offset":5